<br>
The answer to your question depends on which perspective you look at it with.  I'll start out by saying I could care less how difficult the quest is.  They made it easy, so it's easy.  If it was hard it would probably take a lot more resources and time but that doesn't change anything for me.  I didn't create a rogue because the epic was easy..  <br>
<br>
Now getting down to the question -- personally I wouldn't want to do that becuase I won't be fighting those types of mobs for awhile.  However if you look at it from someone who kills these type of mobs I would probably have to say yes.  At that point though, don't most rogues have their Ragebringer bagged anyways?  That makes the question quite irrelevent..<br>
<br>
Either way though, change or not, it won't make that much of a difference to me unless I'm at the top of my game and equipment.    It is an issue though, not a major one, but an issue none the less that should be addressed correctly.   I'm not going to argue that other classes don't have problems that are worse then the small one stated here..  I'm a rogue and this is about rogues,  so I posted my opinion(s).   I'm against additional damage, but I'm all for additional weapons for those rogues that are at that point to keep things balanced.  <br>
<br>
