<br>
Monk FD &gt; rogue evade<br>
<br>
Evade works roughly 50% of the time and drops you to second on the hate list, if you are already second it drops you a further 500 points.  You have to be extremely lucky to get an evade off while under attack, because if you get hit at the wrong time it has absolutely no chance of working.  <br>
<br>
Monk FD works roughly 85% of the time and can completely wipe you from the hate list.  You can also FD while being pummelled.<br>
<br>
Yes I know we have a skill called escape, which if you have enough points to get can be used once every 72 min.  Monks can also use their AA points to make FD work even better.<br>
<br>
Please help me out here Natan, what better rogue weapon than the Mrylokars (Vulak item) dagger is out there?  Because this is what were talking about here.  The best rogue weapons vs. the best monk weapons and the fact that rogues at the very end game are NOT doing 20% more damage than monks it is more like 5-10% more damage and the gap is closing even further.<br>
