<br>
Natan, I understand you need to argue for improvements to your class. HOWEVER, this thread was not started to discuss the damage output of all classes across the board. The main topic being discussed here is (pardon the caps, meant for emphasis) HIGH-END MONK DAMAGE VS. HIGH END ROGUE DAMAGE. As it has been repeatedly pointed out, the discrepency between "end-game" monk damage and rogue damage affects the vast majority of us not..at...all. Why you seem to insist on inferring from this debate that all rogues are complaining that we don't do enough damage is beyond me. I've seen several people post that they are perfectly happy with the class the way it is.<br>
<br>
Wendolyn's post was making the point that, if Verant wants the formula to be warrior = 100%, monk = 120%, and rogue = 140% damage, then they should make that formula true across the board, even as it pertains to high-end weaponry. If this is how it is to be, then a monk with the best weapon in the game should do 20% less damage than a rogue with the best weapon in the game, and that, according to her findings, that is not the case.<br>
<br>
Feel free to join in the debate all you like; but please, try to stay in topic if possible, get your facts straight ("Don't ignore, that you BS every second for over 400 to 800 damage approx. I have to spend A SHITLOAD of mana to do that kind of damage, if you know the word mana." Hmm...my backstab key must be broken, I don't backstab every second, nor do I always backstab for 400+, even assuming I don't miss), and please, for the sake of the making your posts a smidge easier to read, consider using the "spellcheck" feature.<br>
<br>
Nicci<br>
